[2 bladen] [blad 1, recto] Ad [Addendum] 28. Witt Library. P.B.II. Box Religious. Copies after Reinhardt [sic] Adoration:

• Antwerp [...] Abb. 797; 2) A'dam, N°650, Bruckmann 1904; 3)Sands Johnson Sale, 19-20, V, 1926, Ph. N° 250, panel 16 1/2 x 21 1/2 in; 4) Sainctelette Sale, Gal. Royale, Brussels, 23 Nov. 19-- [sic], N° [sic], Bois 37 x 55 cm;

[blad 1, verso] 5) Sale Drouot, Paris, 27-XI-1922, N° 30, B. 43 x 58 cm; 6) Scholl-Riaucourt Sale, Schloss Gausssig; 7) Prague 85 - hat Schneegestöber; 8) Rosenbloom Coll. U.S.A. (see Art News, March 1946); 9) Lord Trevor Coll. Flemish Exh. R.A. 1927, N° 233, Panel 16 x 221/2 in. (40 x 57 cm); 10) Academy Venice; 11) Sankt Lucas, Vienne 1931 (Ph.) &1935 Exh., N° 54, Holz 40 x 57 cm; [blad 2, recto] Ad 28. Copies after Reinhart Adoration continued.

11)[sic] In 1938 with Bamman, Düsseldorf, ex. Graf Waldstein, Prague Von Miller zu Aich[h]olz, Vienna; 12) François Empain, Brussels; 13) Sir Lionel Earle Coll. Exh. Antwerp, Ph. 1930, N° 58, Panel 55 x 75,8 cm;

[blad 2, verso]14) Engelhart Coll. Vienna, Flemish Exh. Vienne, N° 105, Holz 38 x 57 cm; 15) Koninckx Sale, Antwerp 6-7 May 1901, N° 15, B. 36 x 55 cm; 16) Kuhn Sale, Muller, A'dam, 4 June 1929, N° 3, signed and dated P. BREVGHEL 1625 (exhib. in Künstlerhaus Brünn 1925), B. 41 x 58 cm; 17) Imperial Academia Petrograd Von allen diesen Kopien hat nur (J) ein Schnee gestöber.
